## Eutrophication
- Overuse of nitrogenous fertilizer causes algal blooms
	- Algae die and decompose
	- Decomposition causes depletion of oxygen 
	- Hypoxic conditions force fish and other animals to either leave or die
- Consequence of overfertilization
	- Animal waste also contains large amounts of nitrogen and phosphorous

- Coastal regions are affected most by hypoxic conditions
	- Most marine life lives near the coast, this has resulted in many extinctions

- Missisippi river has large dead zone at its mouth since so much farmland drains into it
